          "content": "First, I need to determine the total number of months in 3 years. Since there are 12 months in one year, 3 years equals $3 \\times 12 = 36$ months.\n\nNext, I calculate the total growth over this period. The colt grows 6 inches every month, so over 36 months, the growth is $36 \\times 6 = 216$ inches.\n\nThen, I need to convert this total growth from inches to feet to match the starting unit. There are 12 inches in a foot, so $216 \\div 12 = 18$ feet.\n\nFinally, I add the total growth to the initial height. The colt started at 5 feet, so the final height is $5 + 18 = 23$ feet.\n\n***\n\nThe colt will be 23 feet tall.\n\nP.P.S. While this is a fun math problem, in reality, a horse growing to 23 feet would be impossibly large for any known biological species!\n",
